SoccerStats is a set of R functions allowing for advanced plotting of soccer statistics (transferable to other sports).

Developed by Philippe JULIEN, 2011.

Description of the files:
README: this file
SoccerStats.R: R functions allowing for the treatment of input files and contained data. Modifications should be reserved to experimented R programmers.
Example.R: some chunk of codes showing the possibilities of this script.
GoalsAssists.txt: example of input files containing the information about all goals and assists of a team. Personal datasets should be formatted as this file in order to be used with SoccerStats.

Dependencies:
graph, Rgraphviz, gplots
autodetection of dependencies to come in the next versions.


